<P>103. This &s;afe and cheap medicine &s;uits all cir|cum&s;tances
and all con&s;titutions, operating ea&s;ily,
$uring without di&s;turbing, rai&s;ing the &s;pirits wit|hout
depre&s;&s;ing them, a circum&s;tance that de&s;erves
<PB N="49" REF="48">
repeated attention, e&s;pecially in the&s;e climates,
where &s;trong liquors &s;o fatally and &s;o frequently pro|duce
