<P>122. Tho&s;e volatile &s;alts, that are &s;et free and
rai&s;ed by a gentle heat, may ju&s;tly be &s;uppo&s;ed
e&s;&s;ential<NOTE N="a" PLACE="foot">8.</NOTE>, and to have pre-exi&s;ted in the ve|getable;
whereas the lixivial fixed &s;alts obtained
by the incineration of the &s;ubject, who&s;e natural
